    <h3>Actions</h3>
    <div class="row">
        <p class="col-xs-12 desc">
            Actions are now setup to use Ember's closure actions. When an
            icon recieves a click event it will call the <code>onClick</code>
            property off of <code>attrs</code>.

            If you prefer to use the older style of actions you may do this too,
            there are examples of both below.

            <br/>&nbsp;<br/>

            In either case the event that is passed is a single hash/object which contains
            the following properties: object (aka, "this"), event (click event), and style
            (either "classic" or "closure")
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-2">
            {{ui-icon 'info-circle' cursor=true muted=true size='3x' onClick='iconActionable'}}
        </div>
        <div class="snippet col-xs-10">
            \{{ui-icon 'info-circle' cursor=true muted=true size='3x' onClick='iconActionable'}}
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-2">
            {{ui-icon 'info-circle' value='foobar' cursor=true muted=true size='3x' onClick=(action 'iconActionable') }}
        </div>
        <div class="snippet col-xs-10">
            \{{ui-icon 'info-circle' <strong>value='foobar'</strong> cursor=true muted=true size='3x' onClick=(action 'iconActionable') }}
        </div>
    </div>


    <h3>Aria Support</h3>
    <div class="row">
        <p class="col-xs-12 desc">
          Aria support is provided for the "role", "labeledBy", and "describedBy" properties.
        </p>
        <p class="col-xs-12 desc">
          By default role will be set to "img" for you unless you state that you want a pointer cursor in which case it defaults to "link". You can, however, set it to anything you like by changing the <b>role</b> property on this component.
        </p>
        <p class="col-xs-12 desc">
          The "labeledBy" defaults to the name of the icon -- specifically the first part of the dasherized name -- but you can override that to whatever you like. The "describedBy" property is not set by default but you can see in this example how we've set it (view source).
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-2">
            {{ui-icon 'eye' labeledBy='my label' describedBy='my description' size='3rem'}}
        </div>
        <div class="snippet col-xs-10">
            \{{ui-icon 'eye' labeledBy='my label' describedBy='my description'}}
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-2">
          {{ui-icon 'eye' pointer=true size='3rem'}}
        </div>
        <div class="snippet col-xs-10">
          \{{ui-icon 'eye' pointer=true}}
        </div>
    </div>

</div>
